@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

<div class="container">
    <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="display-4">Welcome to MapHive</h1>
        <p class="lead">A platform for managing and exploring map locations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                    <h3><i class="bi bi-map"></i> Explore Locations</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>Browse all map locations in an interactive map interface. View details of each location and find what you're looking for.</p>
                    <a asp-controller="Map" asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg mt-3">
                        <i class="bi bi-search"></i> View Map
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
                    <h3><i class="bi bi-plus-circle"></i> Add New Locations</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>Contribute to our database by adding new locations. Simply enter the coordinates and provide details about the place.</p>
                    <a asp-controller="Map" asp-action="Add" class="btn btn-success btn-lg mt-3">
                        <i class="bi bi-plus-lg"></i> Add Location
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-3">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                    <h3><i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> About MapHive</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>MapHive is a simple yet powerful application for managing map locations. Built with .NET Core 8 MVC and using Leaflet.js for map rendering, it provides a clean interface for users to interact with geographical data.</p>
                    <p>Key features include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Interactive map display of all locations</li>
                        <li>Simple form for adding new locations</li>
                        <li>Detailed view of each location with all its information</li>
                        <li>Edit and delete functionality for managing existing locations</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div> 